# Prava.ge — Project Architecture

## Overview
Georgian driving license exam preparation platform. Users practice with exam tickets (by category/subject), take timed exams, and review questions.

## Frontend (this repo)
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router) + React 19 + TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4 + Ant Design 6
- **HTTP**: Axios (`src/api/BaseApi.ts`) → `http://localhost:3000` with `withCredentials: true`
- **Path alias**: `@/*` → `./src/*`

### Key Routes
| Route | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/` | Server | Home page (withHeader layout) |
| `/tickets/[category]` | Server | Paginated questions filtered by category + subject |
| `/subjectpicker` | Client | Multi-select subjects before exam |
| `/exam` | Server+Client | Timed exam (30 min, 30 questions, max 3 mistakes) |

### Component Structure
- `TicketsQuiz` — single ticket question display + answer selection
- `ExamQuiz` — full exam flow with navigation, timer, scoring
- `QuizButton` — answer button with correct/incorrect states
- `CategoryCard` — category link card with active state
- `SubjectAsideMenu` / `SubjectMenuCard` — sidebar subject filter (toggleable)
- `TicketPagination` — Ant Design pagination wrapper using URL params
- `ExamFooter` — answer key bar / navigation (shared between exam & tickets)

### State Management
- No global state library. Uses `useState`, URL search params, custom hooks.
- Custom hooks: `useQuizNavigation`, `useExamProgress`, `useArrowNavigation`, `useWindowSize`

## Backend (github.com/lursmana1/nest)
- **Framework**: NestJS 11 + TypeScript
- **Databases**: MongoDB (Mongoose) + MySQL (TypeORM)
- **Auth**: JWT via httpOnly cookies (Passport)
- **Port**: 3000, CORS allows frontend at 3001

### Database Split
| DB | ORM | Stores |
|---|---|---|
| MongoDB | Mongoose | questions, categories, exams |
| MySQL | TypeORM | users, products |

### API Endpoints (used by frontend)
```
GET /categories                              → Category[]
GET /categories/:id                          → Category
GET /questions?category=&subjects=&page=&size= → { items, page, size, total, totalPages }
GET /questions/random?count=&subjects=&category= → Question[]
GET /questions/:id                           → Question
```

### API Endpoints (built, not yet used by frontend)
```
GET    /exams/generate?subjects=&categories=&count= → Exam (saved to DB)
GET    /exams         → Exam[]
GET    /exams/:id     → Exam
POST   /exams         → Exam (manual questionIds)
PATCH  /exams/:id     → Exam
DELETE /exams/:id     → { deleted: true }
POST   /auth/register → { user } + sets access_token cookie
POST   /auth/login    → { user } + sets access_token cookie
POST   /auth/logout   → { ok: true } + clears cookie
```

### MongoDB Schemas
**Question** (`questions` collection): `id, question, question_explained, correct_answer, answer_1-4, subject (number), categories (number[]), hasImg, img, audio`

**Category** (`categories` collection): `id, name, iconKey, questionsCount, subjectCount, subjects[] (embedded: id, name, questionsCount)`

**Exam** (`exams` collection): `title, questions (ObjectId[] ref → Question), timestamps`

### MySQL Entities
**User**: `id, name, email, age, password, products[]`
**Product**: `id, ..., creator (→ User)`

## Conventions
- Server Components for data fetching, Client Components (`"use client"`) for interactivity
- Tailwind classes preferred over inline styles
- Feature-based component folders (component + types in same dir)
- Georgian font: `font-georgian` utility class
- Pagination via URL search params (`page`, `size`, `subjects`)
